commands.name: az ml online-deployment create
commands.summary: Create a deployment. If the deployment already exists, it will fail. If you want to update existing deployment, use az ml online-deployment update.
commands.syntax:
az ml online-deployment create --file
                               --resource-group
                               --workspace-name
                               [--all-traffic]
                               [--endpoint-name]
                               [--local {false, true}]
                               [--local-enable-gpu {false, true}]
                               [--name]
                               [--no-wait]
                               [--package-model]
                               [--set]
                               [--skip-script-validation]
                               [--vscode-debug {false, true}]
                               [--web]
examples: az ml online-deployment create --file deployment.yaml --resource-group my-resource-group --workspace-name my-workspace

commands.name: az ml online-deployment delete
examples: az ml online-deployment delete --name my-deployment --endpoint-name my-endpoint --yes --resource-group my-resource-group --workspace-name my-workspace

commands.name: az ml online-deployment get-logs
commands.summary: Get the container logs for an online deployment.
examples: az ml online-deployment get-logs --name my-deployment --endpoint-name my-endpoint --lines 100 --resource-group my-resource-group --workspace-name my-workspace

commands.name: az ml online-deployment list
examples: az ml online-deployment list --endpoint-name my-endpoint --resource-group my-resource-group --workspace-name my-workspace

commands.name: az ml online-deployment show
examples: az ml online-deployment show --name my-deployment --endpoint-name my-endpoint --resource-group my-resource-group --workspace-name my-workspace

commands.name: az ml online-deployment update
commands.syntax:
az ml online-deployment update --resource-group
                               --workspace-name
                               [--add]
                               [--endpoint-name]
                               [--file]
                               [--force-string]
                               [--local {false, true}]
                               [--local-enable-gpu {false, true}]
                               [--name]
                               [--no-wait]
                               [--remove]
                               [--set]
                               [--skip-script-validation]
                               [--vscode-debug {false, true}]
                               [--web]
examples: az ml online-deployment update --file deployment.yaml --resource-group my-resource-group --workspace-name my-workspace
